    "updated_at": "2015-06-29T19:22:54Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A workaround I've employed previously is to do:\n`Directory.SetCurrentDirectory(Path.GetDirectoryName(Assembly.GetEntryAssembly().Location))` as the first line in `Main` in order to ensure the current directory is actually what you expect. This way if another process launches you with an unexpected current directory all your relative paths don't explode.\n"
  },
